# .mailmap
# Map commit author names and emails to canonical identities for git
# Lines starting with '#' are comments. Each mapping can be in one of these forms:
#
# Proper Name <proper.email@example.com> Wrong Name <wrong.email@example.com>
# Proper Name <proper.email@example.com> <wrong.email@example.com>
# <proper.email@example.com> <wrong.email@example.com>
#
# Examples:
# Alice Smith <alice@example.com> A. Smith <asmith@users.noreply.github.com>
# Bob Jones <bob@example.com> <bob.jones+old@gmail.com>
#
# Add your project-specific mappings below (one per line):

# This is based on the command:
## git log --pretty=format:"%an <%ae>" | sort | uniq -c

